      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CONTRADICTION (3) goes very well this trip starting 21 times for 10 wins and six minors. Recorded a 1.75 lengths win (23.73) in a Grade 4/5 last time at this track. Looks suited and should go close. MY NAME'S EDEN (1) tends to drift back and work into the race, winding up late into second (20.10) in a Grade 4/5 at Traralgon last time and making it three straight placings. Solid record at the distance winning 17 races. Bold showing expected. PAW PRYDI (8) doesn't win out of turn but recent form sound. Has been in the minors the last two runs, the latest finishing second (22.43) at Shepparton. Has never been out of the money in three starts this course. Expected to feature again. BERNARDO BLUE (7) flew the lids and led all the way last time. Must be respected.",
